                    {
                        "unit_id": 4437,
                        "title": "Types of AI: Machine Learning",
                        "slug": "types-of-ai-machine-learning",
                        "order": 20,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "URLQK1Y_GY4",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<audio controls>\r\n  <source src=\"https://educate.potential.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Types-of-AI-Machine-Learning.mp3\" type=\"audio/mp3\">\r\n  Your browser does not support the audio element.\r\n</audio>\r\n\r\n<h5>Machine Learning (ML) is where computers learn from data without being explicitly programmed. </h5>\r\n<h5>There are three primary types:</h5>\r\n<h5>1- supervised (where the system is trained with labeled data, like tagged photos) </h5>\r\n<h5>2- unsupervised (where the system learns patterns from unlabelled data, like identifying customer segments),  </h5>\r\n<h5>3- reinforcement learning (where the system learns by receiving feedback, like a video game AI).  </h5>\r\n<h5>ML models train on datasets and then test their predictions on unseen data.  </h5>",
                            "course-unit-read-more": " <div class=\"embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9\">\r\n    <iframe class=\"embed-responsive-item\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HcqpanDadyQ?si=eHcFFahg2_tNYcDb\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>",
