                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<audio controls>\r\n  <source src=\"https://educate.potential.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Types-of-AI-Deep-Learning.mp3\" type=\"audio/mp3\">\r\n  Your browser does not support the audio element.\r\n</audio>\r\n\r\n<h5>Deep Learning, a subset of ML, uses neural networks with many layers (resembling the human brain) to analyze various data aspects.  </h5>\r\n<h5>While a traditional neural network might recognize an object's shape in a photo, a convolutional neural network (CNN) can identify textures, colors, and other features.  </h5>\r\n<h5>Apps like Replika utilize deep learning for intricate conversations, and platforms like Facebook employ it for facial recognition.  </h5>\r\n<h5>Witness the depth of AI, where machines come eerily close to human-like perception. </h5>",
