                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<audio controls>\r\n  <source src=\"https://educate.potential.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Types-of-AI-Natural-Language-Processing.mp3\" type=\"audio/mp3\">\r\n  Your browser does not support the audio element.\r\n</audio>\r\n\r\n<h5>Natural Language Processing (NLP) bridges the gap between human language and computer understanding.  </h5>\r\n<h5>Key techniques include tokenization (breaking text into words or phrases) and embeddings (converting words into vectors).  </h5> \r\n<h5>Companies employ sentiment analysis, a part of NLP, to gauge customer feedback on social media. Tools like Google Translate assist travelers in understanding foreign languages in real-time, and Grammarly aids in content refinement.  </h5>\r\n<h5>The era where machines truly \"get\" us isn't far.</h5>",
