                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<audio controls>\r\n  <source src=\"https://educate.potential.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Types-of-AI-Generative-AI.mp3\" type=\"audio/mp3\">\r\n  Your browser does not support the audio element.\r\n</audio>\r\n\r\n<h5>Generative AI is all about nurturing AI's inner artist, enabling it to craft fresh content spanning text, images, and music.  \r\n</h5>\r\n<h5>Think of it as AI's creative genius at work. </h5>\r\n<h5>Generative AI achieves this through techniques like Generative adversarial networks (GANs) and Variational Autoencoders (VAEs), where it learns patterns and gives birth to entirely new concepts. </h5>\r\n<h5>Its applications are far-reaching, from sparking creativity in art and generating diverse content to aiding in drug discovery and enhancing data for machine learning. </h5>\r\n<h5>Brace yourself to unlock the imaginative side of AI. </h5>",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "<div class=\"embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9\">\r\n    <iframe class=\"embed-responsive-item\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/pWNAtUwnBS8?si=NqMvaS6u4FIQ7xhp\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>",
